org.eclipse.rdf4j.rio.trig

Class TriGWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.rdf4j.rio.helpers.AbstractRDFWriter
      • org.eclipse.rdf4j.rio.turtle.TurtleWriter
        • org.eclipse.rdf4j.rio.trig.TriGWriter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RDFHandler, RDFWriter

    public class TriGWriter
extends TurtleWriter
    An extension of TurtleWriter that writes RDF documents in TriG format by adding graph scopes to the Turtle document.
    Author:
    Arjohn Kampman

      • handleStatementInternal

        protected void handleStatementInternal(Statement st,
                                       boolean endRDFCalled,
                                       boolean canShortenSubject,
                                       boolean canShortenObject)
        Description copied from class: TurtleWriter
        Internal method that differentiates between the pretty-print and streaming writer cases.
        Overrides:
        handleStatementInternal in class TurtleWriter
        Parameters:
        st - The next statement to write
        endRDFCalled - True if endRDF has been called before this method is called. This is used to buffer statements for pretty-printing before dumping them when all statements have been delivered to us.
        canShortenSubject - True if, in the current context, we may be able to shorten the subject of this statement iff it is an instance of BNode.
        canShortenObject - True if, in the current context, we may be able to shorten the object of this statement iff it is an instance of BNode.
